    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a high-floor offensive profile, anchored by **Gunnar Henderson** (81.88) and **Kyle Tucker** (78.04), both of whom benefit from favorable matchups against mid-rotation arms. **Gunnar Henderson** is our top play, as he draws Wacha in a contest bolstered by wind-out conditions and a significant SP skill gap that elevates his raw projection by 15%. Similarly, **Kyle Tucker** occupies a prime spot in the order, and despite a slight park penalty, his elite xwOBA metrics against right-handed pitching make him a high-conviction start. Meanwhile, **Jackson Merrill** (75.27) provides a massive efficiency boost today, with a 14% park factor and 17% SP-skill adjustment working in concert to make him an essential anchor in the outfield.\n\nPlatoon advantages are the primary engine for our mid-tier producers. **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** (73.66) and **Nasim Nunez** (65.67) both see their scores surge due to a favorable matchup against Fuentes; **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** in particular benefits from a 19% SP-skill adjustment, making him a sneaky candidate for stolen base volume. The most difficult roster decision involved **Marcell Ozuna** (59.52), who narrowly missed the starting cut. While he possesses the requisite power to outperform his projection, the optimizer preferred the high-floor efficiency of **Miguel Vargas** and **Andy Pages**, whose situational variables\u2014specifically lineup positioning and dynamic platoon splits\u2014edged out **Marcell Ozuna** in a tight calculation.\n\nWe are monitoring several \"Lineup Pending\" statuses closely, as the projections for **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Nasim Nunez**, **Brady House**, **Kyle Tucker**, **Jackson Merrill**, **Andy Pages**, and **Miguel Vargas** are predicated on assumed batting orders. Should any of these players drop lower in their respective lineups, their scoring impact will diminish significantly. Furthermore, while **Liam Hicks** (44.89) is in the lineup, his proximity to the 40-point \"below floor\" threshold suggests he is the most volatile asset today, with his value heavily dependent on maintaining his #4 spot to offset his SP-skill penalty. We will proceed with a full-strength lineup, but remain ready to pivot if early weather or confirmed lineup news shifts the efficiency outlook.",
